[2026-05-15T23:43:59Z] Frontend Agent — phase-1 status

Owned scope this phase
- /app/(auth)/sign-up         (mode select + community guidelines acceptance)
- /app/(auth)/mode            (one-account-two-modes switcher)
- /app/profile                (companion profile setup screen)
- /components                 (shared UI primitives — Spinner, StatusMessage)

Inputs consumed (frozen contracts)
- /app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md             (Core API agent — phase 1)
- DTOs from /app/api/profiles/_lib/types.ts (OwnCompanionProfileDTO,
  AvailabilityDTO)
- Auth session helpers from /lib/auth (AuthProvider/useAuth) and
  /lib/auth/session (requireSessionUser, getSessionUser)
- Storage helper /lib/auth/storage#avatarPublicUrl (server-only)

What's wired up
- /sign-up: server action calls Supabase Auth signUp, mirrors
  public.users with chosen modes (seeker/companion) and guideline
  acceptance, then redirects to /verify or /check-email depending on
  whether a session was returned. Displays validation/sign-up errors
  inline. Mobile-first, max-w 26rem card, 44px tap targets.
- /mode: form that flips is_seeker / is_companion via setModesAction,
  with idle/error/ok states and an enforced "at least one mode" guard
  (handled server-side in updateUserModes).
- /profile: server-rendered shell, gated via requireSessionUser →
  redirects to /login (signed out), /verify (no mirror row), or /mode
  (not in companion mode). Renders:
    1. Profile photo card (server-rendered, links to /verify uploader)
    2. <CompanionProfileSetup /> client component
       - Loads /api/profiles/me on mount; distinct loading-skeleton,
         empty (no profile yet → nudge to create), error (Try again),
         and ready states.
       - Edit form: headline, bio, rate (USD cents), currency, meal
         types, lat/lng + "Use my current location" (browser geolocation
         with explicit-permission helper text), service radius. Submits
         PUT /api/profiles/me, surfaces 400/409/etc. error envelopes
         from readError().
       - Verification badge surfaces verification_status read-only;
         rejected/unverified link to /verify (Auth & Identity owns the
         actual verification flow). API never lets us write
         verification_status — respected.
       - Availability card: list (loading skeleton, empty banner, error
         banner), add form with day/meal/start/end/timezone, per-row
         delete. POST/DELETE on /api/profiles/me/availability[/{id}].

Frontend touch added this phase
- Surfaced the current avatar (or placeholder) on /profile with a clear
  "Change photo" / "Upload a photo" link to /verify, where the Auth &
  Identity uploader lives. Avoids forcing companions to leave the
  profile screen to discover the photo step.

Quality
- npm run lint        ✓ clean
- npm run type-check  ✓ clean
- npm run build       ✓ 16/16 routes generated
- npm run test        ✓ 50 unit tests pass (5 files)

Core product rules respected
- Lunch & dinner only: meal_types restricted to MEAL_TYPES enum.
- One account, two modes: sign-up + /mode keep both flags independent
  with at-least-one validation.
- Server-side authority: every mutating call is a server action or hits
  an authenticated API route. The client only renders state and posts
  forms; we never write verification_status or other Auth-owned fields
  from the frontend.
- Verification gating: no Frontend code attempts to bypass RLS-enforced
  hiding of unverified companions. The status banner is read-only.
- Location permission: the "Use my current location" button calls
  navigator.geolocation, which surfaces the browser permission prompt;
  helper text tells the user we'll ask first.
- Card data: no payment UI in this phase.

Interfaces published (Frontend ↔ users)
- /sign-up   GET (form) → submits formData via signUpAction
- /mode      GET (form) → submits formData via setModesAction
- /profile   GET → wires to /api/profiles/me +
                          /api/profiles/me/availability(/[id])

Known gaps / open items
- Avatar upload UI is owned by Auth & Identity (/verify); /profile only
  surfaces and links to it. If we want in-place upload on /profile in a
  later phase, that needs an Orchestrator scope decision.
- Discovery (/discover), companion public profile (/companions/[id]),
  request-a-meal, bookings, chat, safety screen, and Stripe Elements
  are all phase-2+ — not started here.

